JOHANNESBURG - ANC Chairperson, Gwede Mantashe's warned people against hijacking funerals to settle political scores. "When we were coming to this funeral, we were told that one of the worst things that could happen was to use such platforms to settle political battle. Funerals are about celebrating lives of who departed, it's about mourning," said Mantashe. READ: Social media abuzz following Winnie Madikizela-Mandela documentary Mantashe was speaking at the funeral of struggle stalwart Winnie Madikizela-Mandela. Thousands descended at the Orlando Stadium to pay their last respect to the woman affectionately known as the "Mother of the Nation". Madikizela-Mandela died at Johannesburg Milpark Hospital on 1 April 2018. eNCA